properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 1 at 8:06AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
Multiple periods of rainfall over the last several weeks, including
the last several days, has increased soil moisture to high levels
across western Washington. More rainfall is expected today as yet
another system passes through the area with additional rainfall
amounts of generally up to an inch possible. This amount of rain
will put extra pressure on soil instability, leading to an
increased threat of landslides being triggered today.

For more information about current conditions, visit
www.weather.gov/seattle, select Hydrology, and then scroll down for
the links to the landslide information pages.

For more information on landslides, visit the website for the
Washington State Department of Natural Resources landslide
geologic hazards at: http://bit.ly/2mtA3wn

To report landslides, contact you local emergency management.

NWSheadline: CONTINUED RAINFALL TODAY WILL LEAD TO AN INCREASED THREAT OF LANDSLIDES IN WESTERN WASHINGTON
